SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Secretary of State issues decision in c
 hallenge to Kevin Nichols nomination petitions for Androscoggin County She
 riff
DESCRIPTION:Secretary of State issues decision in challenge to Kevin Nicho
 ls nomination petitions for Androscoggin County Sheriff\n<span><span lang=
 "lang">jana.spaulding…</span></span>\n\n<span><time datetime="2026-06-10
 T20:40:46-04:00" title="Wednesday\, June 10\, 2026 - 20:40">Wed\, 06/10/20
 26 - 20:40</time>\n</span>\n\n          <p><time datetime="2026-06-10T12:0
 0:00Z">6/10/2026</time>\n</p>\n    \n  <div>\n                  <div>\n   
        <p><strong>AUGUSTA\, Maine</strong> — Secretary of State Shenna B
 ellows <a href="https://www.maine.gov/sos/sites/maine.gov.sos/files/inline
 -files/KNichols_Andro%20Cty%20Sheriff_Final%20decision%20%28002%29.pdf" ti
 tle="KNichols_Andro Cty Sheriff_Final decision (002).pdf">issued a decisio
 n</a> regarding a challenge to the nomination petitions filed by Kevin Nic
 hols as a non-party candidate for Androscoggin County Sheriff.</p><p>The S
 ecretary of State’s Office received the written challenge from Eric G. S
 amson alleging that Mr. Nichols has no recorded history of holding a super
 visory position as required by Maine statute <a href="https://legislature
 .maine.gov/statutes/30-a/title30-asec371-b.html">30-A M.R.S. §371-B (3)(E
 )</a>. A hearing was held on Wednesday\, June 3 with Deputy Secretary Juli
 e Flynn of the Bureau of Corporations\, Elections and Commissions serving 
 as the Presiding Officer at the Hearing\, and Assistant Attorney General J
 on Bolton assisting as legal counsel.</p><p>The Secretary\, upon review of
  the proceedings and evidence\, determined that Samson met his burden to e
 stablish that Nichols lacks the required supervisory employment experience
 .</p><p>“Based on the proceedings and the evidence\, I agree with the co
 nclusion and recommendation submitted by the hearings officer that Mr. Nic
 hols lacks the supervisory experience required by law to hold this positio
 n.”</p>\n        </div>\n            </div>\nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/n
 ews/secretary-state-issues-decision-challenge-kevin-nichols-nomination-pet
 itions-androscoggin
